1
00:00:09,125 --> 00:00:10,333
[RITSU]
Wow!

2
00:00:10,416 --> 00:00:12,833
Feels neat!

3
00:00:12,916 --> 00:00:15,458
Hey, do you think I'll
be able to do this, too?

4
00:00:15,541 --> 00:00:16,791
[MOB]
Mh-mm!

5
00:00:16,875 --> 00:00:19,125
Of course. After all,
you're my little brother!

6
00:00:19,208 --> 00:00:20,333
[gasps]

7
00:00:27,541 --> 00:00:28,791
[gasps]

8
00:00:34,750 --> 00:00:37,916
[RITSU]
He! Hoo! Ha!

9
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:42,000
[RITSU grunting]

10
00:02:16,708 --> 00:02:17,875
[ARATAKA]
Everything's ready.

11
00:02:17,958 --> 00:02:20,791
We will now begin the séance.

12
00:02:20,875 --> 00:02:22,958
[gulps]

13
00:02:23,041 --> 00:02:24,791
--[ARATAKA grunts]
--[HITOSHI yelps]

14
00:02:28,208 --> 00:02:30,708
Hey, tell me, is that you, Dad?

15
00:02:30,791 --> 00:02:32,875
Do you know who I am?

16
00:02:32,958 --> 00:02:37,250
Oh... Oh! Hitoshi!

17
00:02:37,333 --> 00:02:39,000
I never thought
the day would come

18
00:02:39,083 --> 00:02:40,041
when I would have the chance

19
00:02:40,125 --> 00:02:42,916
to see your face
again, my son.

20
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,625
Oh, Dad.

21
00:02:44,708 --> 00:02:45,875
One thing...

22
00:02:45,958 --> 00:02:47,916
When did you learn to
speak English so well?

23
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:50,208
Click! Loggin' out for a sec.

24
00:02:50,291 --> 00:02:51,583
Huh?

25
00:02:51,666 --> 00:02:52,250
[ARATAKA] Sorry, It doesn't
seem like I'm getting

26
00:02:52,333 --> 00:02:53,708
a very good signal.

27
00:02:53,791 --> 00:02:55,166
Were you satisfied, though?

28
00:02:55,250 --> 00:02:56,166
Of course not!

29
00:02:56,250 --> 00:02:58,000
Please, call him
back this instant!

30
00:02:58,083 --> 00:02:59,916
[ARATAKA]
Whoa! Calm down, buddy!

31
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,750
It takes a lot of concentration
to head up a séance.

32
00:03:02,833 --> 00:03:05,083
By the way, where is
your father from?

33
00:03:05,166 --> 00:03:06,541
He wasn't local?

34
00:03:06,625 --> 00:03:09,166
No, he was from
New Jersey in America.

35
00:03:09,250 --> 00:03:11,625
[ARATAKA] Foreign languages
are automatically translated.

36
00:03:11,708 --> 00:03:12,666
Oh!

37
00:03:12,750 --> 00:03:13,750
It's an advanced
technique that does

38
00:03:13,833 --> 00:03:15,125
something-or-other
to the wavelength

39
00:03:15,208 --> 00:03:16,958
of the spirit's languages
and is hard to master.

40
00:03:17,041 --> 00:03:18,916
But, don't worry, there will
not be an additional fee.

41
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:21,000
Amazing! But my
English isn't bad.

42
00:03:21,083 --> 00:03:22,208
I'm pretty fluent.

43
00:03:22,291 --> 00:03:23,541
Now, then...

44
00:03:24,916 --> 00:03:26,208
Oh! Hey, Hitoshi!

45
00:03:26,291 --> 00:03:28,333
How have things been goin'?

46
00:03:28,416 --> 00:03:29,583
Kinda weird, but...

47
00:03:29,666 --> 00:03:30,833
Whatever.

48
00:03:30,916 --> 00:03:33,291
Hey, Dad. Ya know
when I was young?

49
00:03:33,375 --> 00:03:35,416
You and I used to
play ball together.

50
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:39,666
And we did that one thing that
was popular on TV back then!

51
00:03:39,750 --> 00:03:42,250
Would you do it for
me one last time?

52
00:03:47,666 --> 00:03:48,625
[HITOSHI]
Dad?

53
00:03:51,375 --> 00:03:53,791
Uh... What the heck was that?

54
00:03:53,875 --> 00:03:55,791
That was the
"Cheeseburger Tornado,"

55
00:03:55,875 --> 00:03:57,250
the main character's
special move in

56
00:03:57,333 --> 00:03:58,500
"Junk Food Fighter Michael,"

57
00:03:58,583 --> 00:04:00,583
the super popular
show at the time.

58
00:04:00,666 --> 00:04:01,958
[HITOSHI] Wait...
Dad, what are you talk--?

59
00:04:02,041 --> 00:04:03,666
Get to the point, Hitoshi.

60
00:04:03,750 --> 00:04:05,333
I've come all the way
from the other side.

61
00:04:05,416 --> 00:04:06,833
What do you want?

62
00:04:06,916 --> 00:04:09,208
Well, I...

63
00:04:09,291 --> 00:04:10,375
Aw, screw it!

64
00:04:10,458 --> 00:04:11,875
You were never nice
to me, anyway, Dad!

65
00:04:11,958 --> 00:04:13,416
Cough up the password
to the hidden safe,

66
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:14,458
you stupid old man!

67
00:04:14,541 --> 00:04:15,833
I know there's
a fortune in there!

68
00:04:15,916 --> 00:04:17,458
You're dead so
you don't need it!

69
00:04:17,541 --> 00:04:19,416
Uh, let me see...

70
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:21,458
I believe the password
was my birthday.

71
00:04:21,541 --> 00:04:22,791
Don't give me that
"birthday" crap!

72
00:04:22,875 --> 00:04:24,541
It's thirteen letters
of the alphabet!

73
00:04:24,625 --> 00:04:25,791
With that kind of money,

74
00:04:25,875 --> 00:04:27,500
I'll have enough cash
for the rest of my life!

75
00:04:27,583 --> 00:04:30,208
Oh! Wait a second,
now I remember!

76
00:04:30,291 --> 00:04:32,208
The password is...

77
00:04:33,791 --> 00:04:36,291
"GETAJOBYOUGOODFORNOTHINGBUM"!

78
00:04:36,375 --> 00:04:37,500
[NARRATOR]
Like the Junk Food Fighter,

79
00:04:37,583 --> 00:04:39,666
this is one of
Reigen's special moves:

80
00:04:39,750 --> 00:04:42,125
using his body like a spring,
he smashes his fist

81
00:04:42,208 --> 00:04:44,541
into his opponent's face
with a powerful spin.

82
00:04:44,625 --> 00:04:46,458
[HITOSHI yelps]

83
00:04:46,541 --> 00:04:47,750
Crap! I went too far!

84
00:04:47,833 --> 00:04:50,041
The client's consciousness
logged out!

85
00:04:50,125 --> 00:04:50,875
What happened?

86
00:04:50,958 --> 00:04:52,333
Did you just take him down?

87
00:04:52,416 --> 00:04:56,250
[ARATAKA] Yeah... But,
it was all in self defense.

88
00:04:56,333 --> 00:04:58,208
Self defense, huh?

89
00:04:58,291 --> 00:05:00,958
[ARATAKA]
Yep. Hey, you look kinda pale.

90
00:05:01,041 --> 00:05:02,916
[MOB] If it's in
self defense, is it okay

91
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,583
to shave off someone's hair,

92
00:05:04,666 --> 00:05:07,208
rip off their clothes,
destroy their pride,

93
00:05:07,291 --> 00:05:09,833
make them lose their friends,
and completely demolish

94
00:05:09,916 --> 00:05:11,500
the school they go to?

95
00:05:13,375 --> 00:05:16,541
[ARATAKA] I think that's going
a bit beyond "self defense."

96
00:05:16,625 --> 00:05:19,291
There are some times
when my psychic powers

97
00:05:19,375 --> 00:05:20,833
go outta control.

98
00:05:20,916 --> 00:05:23,791
And it always seems to happen
when I'm unconscious.

99
00:05:23,875 --> 00:05:25,500
I don't want these
powers anymore.

100
00:05:25,583 --> 00:05:26,833
It's too much.

101
00:05:26,916 --> 00:05:30,125
If nothing else, I think
they're quite useful.

102
00:05:30,208 --> 00:05:32,458
The way you use them when you
work as my apprentice?

103
00:05:32,541 --> 00:05:36,250
So many clients have been
helped with those powers.

104
00:05:36,333 --> 00:05:38,000
So don't just focus
on the negatives.

105
00:05:38,083 --> 00:05:41,083
It's all about how you
use those knives, right?

106
00:05:41,166 --> 00:05:42,791
Don't suppress yourself.

107
00:05:42,875 --> 00:05:45,625
You hold the keys, here.
Maximize your potential.

108
00:05:45,708 --> 00:05:46,625
You do that,

109
00:05:46,708 --> 00:05:48,416
and you're gonna
be just fine, Mob.

110
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:49,791
[MOB sighs]

111
00:05:51,666 --> 00:05:52,666
[SALT GANG 4C]
Huh?

112
00:05:52,750 --> 00:05:54,750
The shadow leader
system? Seriously?

113
00:05:54,833 --> 00:05:55,916
[ONIGAWARA]
Yeah.

114
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,708
I completely lost
to that shadow leader

115
00:05:57,791 --> 00:06:00,833
named Hanazawa, but the
guy who bested him

116
00:06:00,916 --> 00:06:02,458
is from Salt Middle School.

117
00:06:02,541 --> 00:06:04,458
[SALT GANG 4B]
No way! Someone that strong?

118
00:06:04,541 --> 00:06:05,833
Yeah.

119
00:06:05,916 --> 00:06:08,500
I'm gonna find him and
make him our shadow leader.

120
00:06:08,583 --> 00:06:09,875
It was you, wasn't it?

121
00:06:09,958 --> 00:06:12,375
You caused the supernatural
stuff at Black Vinegar.

122
00:06:12,458 --> 00:06:13,708
Uh, well, I--

123
00:06:13,791 --> 00:06:15,083
[MEZATO]
You're basically the only person

124
00:06:15,166 --> 00:06:17,500
who could do
something like that.

125
00:06:17,583 --> 00:06:19,125
But according to the rumors,

126
00:06:19,208 --> 00:06:20,916
a kid who goes there
can throw people around

127
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:23,000
just as easily as you do.

128
00:06:23,083 --> 00:06:24,041
Who knows?

129
00:06:24,125 --> 00:06:26,416
Maybe that means
he's an esper, too.

130
00:06:27,500 --> 00:06:30,041
You guys met up at Black Vinegar
and fought, didn't you?

131
00:06:30,125 --> 00:06:31,375
That's it, right?

132
00:06:31,458 --> 00:06:33,833
You two had a
psychic-telekinetic battle!

133
00:06:33,916 --> 00:06:35,333
[TOME]
Twitch, twitch.

134
00:06:35,416 --> 00:06:38,208
You don't wanna talk about it?

135
00:06:38,291 --> 00:06:40,708
That's enough for today, then.

136
00:06:40,791 --> 00:06:43,375
But someday soon, you're
definitely gonna tell me

137
00:06:43,458 --> 00:06:44,833
all I wanna know.

138
00:06:46,708 --> 00:06:47,875
[sighs]

139
00:06:47,958 --> 00:06:48,875
No way!

140
00:06:48,958 --> 00:06:50,666
That wasn't the work of aliens?

141
00:06:50,750 --> 00:06:51,958
And, that aside...

142
00:06:52,041 --> 00:06:53,500
...are there really
espers around here

143
00:06:53,583 --> 00:06:55,958
other than yourself?

144
00:06:56,041 --> 00:06:58,000
Yes, there are.

145
00:06:58,083 --> 00:07:00,125
[TOME chuckles]

146
00:07:00,208 --> 00:07:01,333
[TOME]
And you can find them.

147
00:07:01,416 --> 00:07:04,291
But... He's the only
other one I've ever met.

148
00:07:04,375 --> 00:07:07,166
[TOME] That's strange.
What about your master?

149
00:07:07,250 --> 00:07:08,583
Ah...

150
00:07:08,666 --> 00:07:11,458
Well, actually, I don't sense
anything from my master.

151
00:07:11,541 --> 00:07:13,750
But that's 'cause his
powers aren't psychic,

152
00:07:13,833 --> 00:07:15,291
they're spiritual.

153
00:07:15,375 --> 00:07:16,916
[TOME]
What kind of rule is that?

154
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:19,875
Well, whatever. Let's go
on a date after this.

155
00:07:19,958 --> 00:07:21,291
[MOB]
Huh?

156
00:07:21,375 --> 00:07:23,125
We'll find other
telepathic people!

157
00:07:23,208 --> 00:07:24,916
Then take our first
step toward connecting

158
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:26,750
with life forms in outer space!

159
00:07:26,833 --> 00:07:28,583
Think about it!

160
00:07:28,666 --> 00:07:29,458
But, remember?

161
00:07:29,541 --> 00:07:32,208
I'm not in the Telepathy Club.

162
00:07:32,291 --> 00:07:34,500
Black Vinegar Middle
School's shadow leader?

163
00:07:34,583 --> 00:07:36,083
Yeah, I lost to him.

164
00:07:36,166 --> 00:07:38,833
That guy had some
seriously nice muscles.

165
00:07:38,916 --> 00:07:40,250
Then who was it that beat him?

166
00:07:40,333 --> 00:07:42,916
It was someone from the
Body Improvement Club, right?

167
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:46,875
He's a gentleman who usually has
quite a distaste for violence.

168
00:07:46,958 --> 00:07:50,750
Do not involve him
in this. Be gone.

169
00:07:50,833 --> 00:07:52,500
Damn that Musashi.

170
00:07:52,583 --> 00:07:53,750
Huh?

171
00:07:53,833 --> 00:07:54,500
Hey...

172
00:07:54,583 --> 00:07:56,333
[gasps] Um, yes?

173
00:07:56,416 --> 00:07:57,666
You were picked on by the guys

174
00:07:57,750 --> 00:08:00,041
from Black Vinegar Middle
School last week, right?

175
00:08:00,125 --> 00:08:01,666
Well, that was all my fault.

176
00:08:01,750 --> 00:08:03,041
Sorry, okay?

177
00:08:03,125 --> 00:08:04,125
Huh? What do you...

178
00:08:04,208 --> 00:08:06,083
I apologized! Just
leave it at that!

179
00:08:06,166 --> 00:08:07,666
I'm sorry, Kageyama.

180
00:08:07,750 --> 00:08:09,916
Tenga's kind of a dummy.
He can't explain things--

181
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,791
[ONIGAWARA]
Shut up!

182
00:08:11,875 --> 00:08:13,416
Stupid idiot!

183
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:16,458
I'm the one talking to him,
so just stay out of it!

184
00:08:17,625 --> 00:08:18,791
[TOKUGAWA]
Well, then...

185
00:08:18,875 --> 00:08:20,125
It appears that will be all

186
00:08:20,208 --> 00:08:23,000
the student council's
activities for this month.

187
00:08:23,083 --> 00:08:25,750
Is that all right,
President Kamuro?

188
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:27,416
[SHINJI]
I'm glad you asked.

189
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:29,958
It's not bad for a start,
but I think we need

190
00:08:30,041 --> 00:08:32,125
something with
a bit more impact.

191
00:08:32,208 --> 00:08:34,791
Right, first year Kageyama?

192
00:08:34,875 --> 00:08:36,041
[gasps]

193
00:08:36,125 --> 00:08:38,041
You rank as one of the
smartest in the nation,

194
00:08:38,125 --> 00:08:40,708
so I want to hear your opinion.

195
00:08:40,791 --> 00:08:41,833
[RITSU]
Well...

196
00:08:41,916 --> 00:08:43,833
In our school, there
are a few students

197
00:08:43,916 --> 00:08:46,250
who would be classified
as delinquents.

198
00:08:46,333 --> 00:08:48,291
If the student council
could find a way

199
00:08:48,375 --> 00:08:50,916
to reprimand them, I think
we'd be able to create

200
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,791
a more peaceful
school environment.

201
00:08:52,875 --> 00:08:53,875
That sounds nice.

202
00:08:53,958 --> 00:08:55,958
"A more peaceful school."

203
00:08:56,041 --> 00:08:58,541
Yes. Let's do that.

204
00:08:59,666 --> 00:09:01,833
[RITSU] I have to make it
a more comfortable place

205
00:09:01,916 --> 00:09:04,000
for my brother.

206
00:09:04,083 --> 00:09:05,666
[MITSUURA]
Kageyama, I presume?

207
00:09:07,708 --> 00:09:09,000
[MITSUURA]
Thank goodness.

208
00:09:09,083 --> 00:09:11,708
Guess there was a point
in waiting around after all.

209
00:09:11,791 --> 00:09:14,000
Let me present my credentials.

210
00:09:14,083 --> 00:09:15,833
[RITSU]
Awakening Lab?

211
00:09:15,916 --> 00:09:17,666
[MITSUURA]
So, what do you think?

212
00:09:17,750 --> 00:09:19,333
Why not give it a try?

213
00:09:19,416 --> 00:09:22,000
This is an opportunity to
amplify your psychic powers

214
00:09:22,083 --> 00:09:24,208
at my research facility!

215
00:09:24,291 --> 00:09:27,708
[RITSU] Sounds like he's got
me confused with my brother.

216
00:09:27,791 --> 00:09:29,416
Ah! Tome, take a look--

217
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:31,291
What is it? Another esper?!

218
00:09:31,375 --> 00:09:32,833
[MOB]
No, I just thought this guy

219
00:09:32,916 --> 00:09:34,500
had a really unique hairstyle.

220
00:09:34,583 --> 00:09:36,250
Oh, wow! You're so right.

221
00:09:37,958 --> 00:09:39,750
Stop fooling around already.

222
00:09:39,833 --> 00:09:42,083
[MOB]
But... I was being serious.

223
00:09:45,125 --> 00:09:47,166
[TOKUGAWA]
Oh, it's you, Kageyama.

224
00:09:47,250 --> 00:09:50,208
Ah, Vice President Tokugawa.

225
00:09:50,291 --> 00:09:51,375
[TOKUGAWA]
Loitering, huh?

226
00:09:51,458 --> 00:09:53,333
I guess even people like you

227
00:09:53,416 --> 00:09:55,333
feel like doing that
from time to time.

228
00:09:55,416 --> 00:09:56,541
Like me?

229
00:09:56,625 --> 00:09:58,333
I'm just an average
middle school student

230
00:09:58,416 --> 00:09:59,666
you can find anywhere.

231
00:09:59,750 --> 00:10:01,833
A totally simple and normal guy.

232
00:10:01,916 --> 00:10:03,333
If you ask me, you won't find

233
00:10:03,416 --> 00:10:05,583
a "totally simple" and
"normal" middle schooler

234
00:10:05,666 --> 00:10:07,333
anywhere on this planet.

235
00:10:07,416 --> 00:10:08,875
But, for whatever reason,

236
00:10:08,958 --> 00:10:12,333
you want to be one and are still
trying to act out the part.

237
00:10:12,416 --> 00:10:15,250
I'm not really sure I
understand what you're saying.

238
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:16,750
[TOKUGAWA] Despite having
abilities that would

239
00:10:16,833 --> 00:10:19,041
always make you the
center of attention,

240
00:10:19,125 --> 00:10:21,083
you consistently seem
to play the minor role

241
00:10:21,166 --> 00:10:23,333
and let others
take the spotlight.

242
00:10:25,375 --> 00:10:27,583
[TOKUGAWA]
Stop acting like your brother.

243
00:10:38,458 --> 00:10:40,791
Hey, Captain! Kageyama's down!

244
00:10:40,875 --> 00:10:42,958
[gasps] No, I'm fine.

245
00:10:43,041 --> 00:10:44,291
Nice drive!

246
00:10:44,375 --> 00:10:46,000
I think you're starting
to build up some stamina!

247
00:10:56,083 --> 00:10:57,833
[RITSU]
Awakening Lab...

248
00:10:57,916 --> 00:10:59,041
This place?

249
00:10:59,125 --> 00:11:00,833
It's just an apartment complex--

250
00:11:00,916 --> 00:11:04,958
Kageyama, you're here!
I'm so glad you showed up!

251
00:11:05,041 --> 00:11:06,458
There's no research
facility here.

252
00:11:06,541 --> 00:11:07,625
You lied to me!

253
00:11:07,708 --> 00:11:09,750
[MITSUURA]
Now, now, just come in.

254
00:11:12,125 --> 00:11:13,333
[MITSUURA]
Welcome!

255
00:11:15,250 --> 00:11:18,333
[MITSUURA]
I call it the Awakening Lab!

